description.narrative: The Action aims to improve the inclusiveness and sustainability of Agriculture VC development in Vietnam to expand livelihoods options of small scale producers in quantity and in quality. Oxfam, a rights-based organisation, brings to the Action its strong experience and on-going initiatives in strengthening resilient, capacity development SSPs, strengthening civil society organisations, convening multi-stakeholder platforms and undertaking policy development and advocacy at all levels. Oxfam brings to the Action experience in facilitating public-private alliances (cocoa, pork). Its main role in the Action will be overall management, brokering and facilitating partnership and cooperation among actors, capacity building, research and policy development/advocacy, and expertise in international human rights and global sustainability standards.

participating-org.narrative: In Vietnam , Oxfam is one of the leading international, non -governmental organisation. Since 1955, Oxfam is active in Vietnam withhumanitarian interventions and started development work in the late 1980's. Today, Oxfam works in 26 provinces with people, governments and civil society to promote equality and well-being through social and economic change.
